  "description": [
    "ms RISE OF BRITISH LABOR IS HELD MARX TRIUMPH Special to The Leader PRAGUEAn article in a recent issue of the new periodical Przitom nost entitled An Impromptu History and signed T G M is being attri buted to Iresident T G Masaryk and for this reason receives unusual attention in the European press Beginning with the remark that Labor Premier MacDonald came into power at the time when Lenin was dying the author reflects on the truth of the saying that the World war meant the world revolution The greatest world empire the British now has a Socialist govern ment and the greatest European em pire the Russian has been under Communist rule for five years It is not possible for millions of European and American men to mur der each other for years without re flecting about it and coming to the conclusion that the system which bred the World war is untenable tiie author continues Not only the soldiers but also their families at home thought about it for these families had occasion to see much more intenstively through the war and its horrors than the men in the field who were too busy to philoso phize"
  ],
